<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8162587>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Habitus (A–B, D–G), male aedeagus (C) and female ovipositors (H) of Coomaniella sunfengyii Liao, Su, Qi & Song, sp. nov. A–C, male, holotype, 6.89 mm, Yongan, Fujian; D, male, paratype, 7.45 mm, Sanming, Fujian; E–G, females, paratypes, 6.37–10.29 mm, Yongan, Fujian. A, C–E, G, dorsal view; B, F, H, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8162587/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8162589>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Male tarsus details of Coomaniella sunfengyii Liao, Su, Qi & Song, sp. nov., holotype (except F). A–C, protarsus; D, mesotarsus; E, metatarsus; F, apex of female metatibia. A, D–E, dorsal view; B, F, lateral view; C, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8162589/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8162591>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Habitat and host plant of Coomaniella sunfengyii Liao, Su, Qi & Song, sp. nov. A, natural habitat (Mr. Feng-Yi Sun is collecting specimens of the new species, the tall tree left behind is Melia azedarach and the trees he pointed are Castanopsis sclerophylla); B, a male in the natural state stay on C. sclerophylla leaves (not true host plant); C, marginal feedings on the leaves of M. azedarach." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8162591/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

